<answer>The main advantages of organizing a firm as a corporation include no limit on the number of owners, limited liability for shareholders, and perpetual existence. The main disadvantages include double taxation, lengthy application process, rigid formalities, and potential for corporate liabilities to be passed on to the owners.</answer>